The paper deals with channel coding and source coding problems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of partial side information and the derivation of capacity and rate-distortion functions suggest that the paper may also belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the use of convex optimization tools and the formulation of a Lagrange dual as a geometric program suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
